sentences: Yogini Joglekar (6 Aug 1925 – 1 November 2005) was a Marathi writer, poet and also a classical singer.
Yogini was born in Pune in 1925 and completed her school education in B.A.
She was working as teacher between 1948 and 1953.
She died on 1 November 2005 at the age of 80 due to prolonged disease.
